Description 1: Identifies the data as being produced from the 2017-2021 American Community Survey.
Geographic summary level code.

Unique geographic id. Digits 1-3 indicate the summary level. Digits 4-7 indicate the component. Digits 8-9 always say US. The remainder varies by summary level. For instance, at summary level 050 (counties), there are 5 digits to indicate the state and county.
The name of the jurisdiction.
State FIPS code. 2 digits.
County FIPS code. 3 digits. Included only in files at summary level 050, 060, 140, and 155.
Minor Civil Division FIPS code. 5 digits. Included only in files at summary level 060.
Place FIPS code. 5 digits. Included only in files at summary level 155 and 160.
Consolidated City FIPS code. 5 digits. Included only in files at summary level 170.
Census tract FIPS code. 6 digits. Included only in files at summary level 140.
